criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  ASA physical status I-III;

          -  18-85 years of age, inclusive;

          -  surgery less than 3 hours.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  indication for catheter insertion;

          -  contraindications to brachial plexus block (e.g., allergy to local anaesthetics,
             malignancy or infection in the area);

          -  existing neurological deficit in the area to be blocked;

          -  pregnancy;

          -  history of neck surgery or radiotherapy;

          -  severe respiratory disease;

          -  chest deformity;

          -  inability to understand the informed consent and demands of the study;

          -  patient refusal.
